commitResults.messageTitle: Change deletetask to delete multiple task
commitResults.messageBody:
User with lots of task on hand may finish lots of task at once

Lets allow the user to delete multiple tasks from the same person at
once

Deleting the same task twice makes no sense. It causes the next task
to be deleted which is bad.

Let's:
* Use sets instead

Notes:
* Duplicate task index in `deletecommand` now causes only that 1 of
those to be parsed
To indicate duplciates in HashSet

User may have some people who needs to be remembered more than others.

Some people are just more important than others!

Lets:
* Allow user to mark those important people in their life

commitResults.messageBody:
The current help command only shows the link to the user guide and
makes it necessary for a new user to go outside of the application to
know how to start using it.

This makes getting to know the basics of the application unnecessarily
tedious as the user has to go to an external source of information.

Implementing a list of instructions inside the app will make the
process of trying to understand the basics as a new user much simpler.
